1
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:29,706
[Episode 31]

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,739
<i>Sorry, the subscriber you dialed is turned off.</i>

3
00:01:34,739 --> 00:01:37,760
<i>Sorry, the subscriber...</i>

4
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,519
Look what you did!

5
00:01:51,519 --> 00:01:53,120
- Mr. Tao.
- At the dock,

6
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,760
if Mr. Liu checks the goods
and they're wrong, who takes the blame?

7
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:58,920
- Sorry.
- Don't just stand there! Pick them up.

8
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,239
Enough, Mr. Tao.

9
00:02:01,239 --> 00:02:03,000
Everyone is watching.

10
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:06,859
Once it's on the ship,
then it's your responsibility.

11
00:02:06,859 --> 00:02:09,660
Until then, you don't get to bark orders here.

12
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:11,600
Got it.

13
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:21,940
Just get the goods to Mr. Liu's dock safely,
and make sure the cops don't catch you.

14
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:29,680
Load the cargo.

15
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,200
Thanks, Yi.

16
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:45,680
Hurry up. Once this last batch is loaded,
we leave.

17
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:31,920
Before we board the ship,
isn't Mr. Tao in charge of the convoy?

18
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,780
Today's different.

19
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:37,300
With you driving alone, I'll feel safe.

20
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:42,260
Phone.

21
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:50,800
- You don't trust me.
- I have rules. You know how it is.

22
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,440
Of course.

23
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,420
Once this run is done,

24
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:14,280
I want to find a place with some sunlight
and get some real rest.

25
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:18,340
Once you're making more and more money,

26
00:04:18,340 --> 00:04:21,840
you won't even want a single day off.

27
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:28,400
Let's go.

28
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,120
Yi.

29
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:42,300
Do you remember when we first met?

30
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:45,159
In 2003. In District Seven.

31
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:49,980
If you hadn't put me in that pool match,

32
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:52,093
I couldn't have supported my family.

33
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,580
No.

34
00:05:55,720 --> 00:06:01,280
The first time we met was under that bridge.

35
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:19,800
If you hadn't helped me back then,
there might not be the me you see today.

36
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:22,060
You saved my life.

37
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,820
I gave you a job in return.

38
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:27,400
Wouldn't you call that fate?

39
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,200
Absolutely.

40
00:06:31,258 --> 00:06:35,100
- I owe you a thank-you, Mr. Zhang.
- No need to thank me.

41
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:43,760
I started out on the street, too.

42
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:46,500
I had a roast goose stall back then.

43
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:52,500
I worked until four or five every morning
for an extra 40 or 50 yuan.

44
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,160
Now.

45
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:06,180
This car you're driving
is worth over a million.

46
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:09,700
No one in Teng City can afford it.

47
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:12,040
But don't worry.

48
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,580
You'll drive something even better.

49
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:22,520
In life, it all comes down to one word: gamble.

50
00:07:32,779 --> 00:07:34,380
<i>Cheers.</i>

51
00:07:39,399 --> 00:07:42,060
<i>When will this hellish life end?</i>

52
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:44,766
<i>These days, seeing geese makes me sick.</i>

53
00:07:45,459 --> 00:07:47,080
<i>Feel good?</i>

54
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:54,660
<i>A few days ago,
my mom took me to see a fortune teller.</i>

55
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:59,320
<i>He read my bone structure
and said that in the next few years,</i>

56
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:03,819
<i>I'd be rich and powerful
and reach the peak of my life.</i>

57
00:08:03,819 --> 00:08:06,199
<i>What kind of fortune teller?</i>

58
00:08:06,199 --> 00:08:07,399
<i>A blind man.</i>

59
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:09,660
<i>You believe a blind man?</i>

60
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:14,040
<i>Fine. I believe him.</i>

61
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:16,580
<i>I'm betting the blind man wins.</i>

62
00:08:24,259 --> 00:08:26,660
Later, my bet paid off.

63
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:28,140
It wasn't the blind man I trusted.

64
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:31,720
It was Zhai Feng Mao's prized brotherhood.

65
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:35,020
He listened to me and trusted me in everything.

66
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:37,020
We started committing tax fraud.

67
00:08:37,020 --> 00:08:41,340
The stakes kept getting higher,
and the money kept pouring in.

68
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:45,900
Then, later,
the whole thing came crashing down.

69
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:50,220
With just a few words, I got Zhai Feng Mao
to take the fall. He did it willingly.

70
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:54,100
As for me, I stayed completely clean.

71
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,100
Over the years,

72
00:08:56,100 --> 00:09:00,980
I became a Teng City entrepreneur
and a great philanthropist.

73
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:04,480
That's why I dare to gamble.

74
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:10,200
Everything I have came from gambling.

75
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:16,180
This time, we have to win this bet.

76
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:18,240
Yi, remember this.

77
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,220
As long as you can win,

78
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:24,780
you can give up everything.

79
00:09:45,659 --> 00:09:47,400
Come on. This way.

80
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,760
What's going on?

81
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,280
- Over here.
- Keep driving forward.

82
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,040
[Drunk Driving Checkpoint]
Hello, sir. Please cooperate.

83
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,320
Blow into this.

84
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,340
What's going on?
Why another drunk-driving checkpoint?

85
00:09:55,340 --> 00:09:56,519
I don't know.

86
00:09:56,519 --> 00:09:58,720
They never check this road.

87
00:09:58,720 --> 00:09:59,940
Yet now...

88
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:03,360
- This is so annoying.
- We're running out of time.

89
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,220
Come on, pull forward.

90
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,600
- Hello?
<i>- Mr. Zhang.</i>

91
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,680
<i>Looks like there's a checkpoint up ahead.</i>

92
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,620
A checkpoint?

93
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:49,820
Traffic police or regular police?

94
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:51,420
Looks like a drunk-driving checkpoint.

95
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:53,440
We're about to pass through.

96
00:10:54,660 --> 00:10:56,640
Tell everyone to stay calm.

97
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:59,419
If they panic, they'll give themselves away.

98
00:10:59,419 --> 00:11:01,900
Okay, got it.

99
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,120
Okay. No problem.

100
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:15,880
Drive safely at night.

101
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:53,180
Okay. Drive safely at night.

102
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:07,680
Routine inspection. Let me check your vehicle.

103
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:24,280
<i>Mr. Zhang, something's wrong.
I saw Zhou Kang An.</i>

104
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:26,200
Switch to the backup plan.

105
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,440
Stop him! Get out!

106
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,020
Get out. Get out of the car.

107
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:42,620
Out. Get out of the car.

108
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:44,180
Hurry up.

109
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,980
Turn right. Take the side road.

110
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:00,960
Get out of the car.

111
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,660
That sly old fox.

112
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:18,000
Teams One and Two,
retrace his route and find him.

113
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,539
Teams Three and Four, secure the scene
and contact the Coast Guard detachment.

114
00:13:20,539 --> 00:13:22,419
We can't pinpoint the suspect's location.

115
00:13:22,419 --> 00:13:24,019
- Hands on your head. Down.
- But he may well

116
00:13:24,019 --> 00:13:27,240
try to escape by sea.
Once he's spotted, intercept him immediately.

117
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,740
Yes.

118
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:47,420
<i>Don't move.</i>

119
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:50,419
<i>Don't make it about belief.</i>

120
00:13:50,419 --> 00:13:52,700
<i>It's just for peace of mind.</i>

121
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,080
<i>I didn't say I'd throw it away.</i>

122
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,460
<i>We don't need divine protection.</i>

123
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:58,660
<i>From now on, we'll be safe and sound.</i>

124
00:13:58,660 --> 00:14:00,120
<i>Okay.</i>

125
00:14:12,639 --> 00:14:14,020
- Hello?
- Hello, Uncle Zhou.

126
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,300
<i>- Jing.</i>
- I saw Zhang Bin's car.

127
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:18,340
<i>- What?</i>
- It turned right at the highway entrance

128
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:19,620
and took a side road.

129
00:14:19,620 --> 00:14:22,500
The plate number is Teng SQ7583.

130
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,759
Did you follow them here?

131
00:14:23,759 --> 00:14:26,039
<i>Chen Yi is in the car too.</i>

132
00:14:26,039 --> 00:14:28,280
This is reckless.

133
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,379
Send out the suspect vehicle's details.

134
00:14:33,379 --> 00:14:35,440
Teng SQ7583.

135
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,760
Keep an eye on that car!

136
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:51,920
You set me up.

137
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:57,141
What do you mean, Bin?

138
00:15:07,780 --> 00:15:10,080
You set me up.

139
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,940
No way.

140
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:44,280
They caught up this fast?

141
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:49,180
Turn left onto the main road.

142
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:54,640
Turn left.

143
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,680
It's not a police car.

144
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:26,600
You siblings make a pretty good team.

145
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,540
Come on, then.

146
00:16:35,419 --> 00:16:37,440
Speed up.

147
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,640
Speed up.

148
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:53,601
Speed up.

149
00:18:48,339 --> 00:18:50,000
Chen Yi.

150
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:02,120
[Luomei Pier, Fishing Harbor Pier]

151
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:03,560
Hello, Uncle Zhou.

152
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:05,036
<i>Jing, don't do anything rash.</i>

153
00:19:05,036 --> 00:19:06,320
Where are you?

154
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:09,220
<i>I'm at the junction of Luomei Pier
and Fishing Harbor Pier.</i>

155
00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:10,480
<i>I lost them.</i>

156
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:14,880
<i>But judging by their route,</i>
they're probably headed to Fishing Harbor Pier.

157
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,380
They're going out to sea.

158
00:19:16,380 --> 00:19:20,100
Near Fishing Harbor Pier,
there's a cluster of abandoned warehouses.

159
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:24,540
If Zhang Bin is running,
going by sea is the safest option.

160
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,980
Jing, stay where you are.

161
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:29,400
<i>I'm on my way.</i>

162
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,920
Okay.

163
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:34,760
Captain Wu, Tech says
the roads near the fishing harbor

164
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:37,500
aren't covered by the traffic cameras
on the national highway.

165
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:41,280
Captain Zhou, there are no cameras
near the fishing harbor.

166
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,299
Take Team Three and search the fishing harbor.

167
00:19:43,299 --> 00:19:45,340
Zhang, take Team One to Luomei.

168
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:47,940
Everyone, stay in contact
with the tech team at all times.

169
00:19:47,940 --> 00:19:49,420
Be careful.

170
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:50,700
- Keep your comms open.
- Yes, sir.

171
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:51,960
- Understood.
- Kai, get in the car.

172
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,460
Let's go.

173
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:05,800
[Unknown Number]

174
00:20:08,019 --> 00:20:11,540
Hello? Sorry. We're closed.

175
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:18,360
It's for you.

176
00:20:21,740 --> 00:20:23,079
Hello?

177
00:20:23,079 --> 00:20:25,759
You've got a chance to get back at Zhang Bin.

178
00:20:25,759 --> 00:20:27,580
Do you want it?

179
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,020
<i>Where is he?</i>

180
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:32,460
Only you would know that.

181
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:35,740
You know him.

182
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:39,760
If he was going to run, where would he go?

183
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:56,120
Zhai, where are you going?

184
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:06,580
To see an old friend.

185
00:21:06,580 --> 00:21:08,200
Go to bed early.

186
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:10,020
Don't wait up.

187
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:15,020
Come back soon.

188
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:38,020
Jing.

189
00:21:42,079 --> 00:21:43,620
Jing.

190
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,600
Hurry.

191
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,079
Search the area. Move.

192
00:21:48,079 --> 00:21:49,640
Okay.

193
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:44,756
<i>You're back late.</i>

194
00:22:53,579 --> 00:22:55,023
<i>Where's Miao Jing?</i>

195
00:22:57,360 --> 00:23:00,740
<i>Your girlfriend was worried about you.</i>

196
00:23:00,740 --> 00:23:02,616
<i>She went to buy medicine.</i>

197
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:15,503
<i>Give me the ledger.</i>

198
00:23:22,119 --> 00:23:23,676
<i>You want it?</i>

199
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:28,683
<i>I said give me the ledger.</i>

200
00:23:30,819 --> 00:23:31,870
<i>Fine.</i>

201
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,366
<i>500,000 yuan.</i>

202
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:38,396
<i>I need to set up a life for my family and me.</i>

203
00:23:53,420 --> 00:23:56,480
<i>A deal works for both of us.</i>

204
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:04,760
<i>Cash, then.</i>

205
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:06,496
<i>Wait for my call.</i>

206
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,496
<i>If you lay a finger on her,</i>

207
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:17,030
<i>you'll never get the other half
of that case file.</i>

208
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:25,280
<i>Young man.</i>

209
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:27,780
<i>We're pretty much the same now.</i>

210
00:24:27,780 --> 00:24:30,340
<i>You know how to negotiate.</i>

211
00:24:30,860 --> 00:24:33,680
<i>Before you said that,</i>

212
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:37,150
<i>I thought you were an undercover cop.</i>

213
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:12,320
<i>Hello.</i>

214
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:14,660
<i>Zhai Feng Mao came to see me.</i>

215
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:16,330
<i>You can move in now.</i>

216
00:25:18,580 --> 00:25:20,420
<i>I applied to Teng City Normal University.</i>

217
00:25:20,420 --> 00:25:22,063
<i>What gave you the right to change it?</i>

218
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,840
<i>There's 80,000 yuan inside.</i>

219
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:27,440
<i>It should be enough for you.</i>

220
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:31,496
<i>Didn't you say everything was fine?
Why are you sending me away now?</i>

221
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:38,960
<i>I'm just tired of all this.</i>

222
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:42,180
<i>We're not on the same path. You can't help me.</i>

223
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:43,980
<i>Chen Yi, are you out of your mind?</i>

224
00:25:43,980 --> 00:25:46,540
<i>Do you hear what you're saying?</i>

225
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:54,120
<i>Of course, I know what I'm doing.</i>

226
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,880
<i>Miao Jing.</i>

227
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:57,983
<i>You'd better wake up soon, too.</i>

228
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:06,500
<i>Do you see it now?</i>

229
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:15,683
<i>Chen Yi.</i>

230
00:26:17,607 --> 00:26:19,363
<i>Don't regret this.</i>

231
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:36,540
<i>Yi.</i>

232
00:26:37,380 --> 00:26:39,380
<i>A couple of days won't make a difference.</i>

233
00:26:39,380 --> 00:26:41,776
<i>Why rush to kick her out?</i>

234
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:47,140
<i>If she doesn't leave, I can't rest easy.</i>

235
00:27:01,859 --> 00:27:03,033
<i>Chen Yi.</i>

236
00:27:24,019 --> 00:27:25,383
<i>Yi.</i>

237
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:28,470
<i>I know this has been hard on you.</i>

238
00:27:30,019 --> 00:27:31,600
<i>Listen.</i>

239
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:33,599
<i>I've thought it over.</i>

240
00:27:33,599 --> 00:27:36,980
<i>This place isn't safe.</i>

241
00:27:36,980 --> 00:27:39,743
<i>I'll take you somewhere new to start over.</i>

242
00:27:40,359 --> 00:27:44,579
<i>Once we make it big,
we'll come home in style, okay?</i>

243
00:27:45,460 --> 00:27:48,880
<i>- What are you trying to say?
- Where are you taking me?</i>

244
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:50,220
<i>Country Jin.</i>

245
00:27:50,220 --> 00:27:51,360
<i>It's close.</i>

246
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,183
<i>Just a few hours away.</i>

247
00:27:58,300 --> 00:28:01,860
<i>Just a few hours away.</i>

248
00:28:14,259 --> 00:28:15,300
<i>Bin.</i>

249
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:18,080
<i>I did everything you asked.</i>

250
00:28:18,080 --> 00:28:19,740
<i>Right.</i>

251
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:23,000
<i>This whole thing is between the three of us.</i>

252
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:25,720
<i>It's too risky to leave him here.</i>

253
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:27,240
<i>I'll take him with me.</i>

254
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:29,020
<i>You're right.</i>

255
00:28:29,020 --> 00:28:32,140
<i>I don't feel good
about you going to Country Jin alone.</i>

256
00:28:32,140 --> 00:28:35,129
<i>I'll handle the case file.</i>

257
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:39,720
<i>Once things blow over,
I'll come get you myself.</i>

258
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:40,940
<i>Okay.</i>

259
00:28:40,940 --> 00:28:42,760
<i>Take care.</i>

260
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,253
<i>Go on.</i>

261
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:10,986
Chen Yi.

262
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,800
I just want to ask you one thing.

263
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:17,530
What exactly did Zhou Kang An promise you?

264
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:22,703
Money, power, status. I can give you all of it.

265
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:25,450
What are you really after?

266
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:29,860
Why team up with Zhou Kang An to betray me?

267
00:30:32,780 --> 00:30:39,180
Because you and I were never on the same path.

268
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,096
You know nothing!

269
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,383
The best path is the one that pays.

270
00:30:50,819 --> 00:30:53,383
So, for money,

271
00:30:54,980 --> 00:30:57,160
you can make

272
00:30:57,160 --> 00:31:00,876
the brother who built all this with you
from the ground up take the fall?

273
00:31:12,539 --> 00:31:14,943
Since you know everything,

274
00:31:19,820 --> 00:31:21,700
things finally add up.

275
00:31:21,700 --> 00:31:24,720
You've been avoiding me
since you came back to Teng City.

276
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,370
So that's what it was all for.

277
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,723
I used to follow Zhai Feng Mao.

278
00:31:40,380 --> 00:31:43,340
He was just a roast-goose-selling nobody.

279
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:45,360
We made it this far.

280
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:48,416
People used to call me Roast Goose Kid,

281
00:31:49,420 --> 00:31:51,410
then Bin,

282
00:31:52,700 --> 00:31:54,403
then Mr. Zhang.

283
00:31:58,460 --> 00:31:59,560
And now,

284
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:04,100
the people
who know my past are pretty much dead.

285
00:32:04,100 --> 00:32:06,010
You're the only one left.

286
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:09,100
Yi.

287
00:32:09,100 --> 00:32:14,036
If you die here today, will you regret it?

288
00:32:17,620 --> 00:32:19,909
You got He Wen Jie killed.

289
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:24,763
You destroyed countless families in Teng City.

290
00:32:27,300 --> 00:32:29,883
You've been a villain half your life.

291
00:32:30,820 --> 00:32:34,040
What do you have besides money?

292
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:35,503
Zhang Bin.

293
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:38,190
Do you regret it?

294
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:44,336
I told you before.

295
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:51,140
I won everything I have now by gambling.

296
00:32:52,100 --> 00:32:54,123
What do I have to regret?

297
00:33:09,220 --> 00:33:11,406
Since you're so eager to suffer,

298
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:15,200
look at me.

299
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:16,340
Look at me.

300
00:33:16,340 --> 00:33:17,860
Come on.

301
00:33:17,860 --> 00:33:20,283
Go down there and take your time.

302
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:41,500
<i>What are you staring at?</i>

303
00:33:41,500 --> 00:33:43,743
<i>Go wash your hands. Dinner's ready.</i>

304
00:33:46,220 --> 00:33:47,943
<i>It's Mom.</i>

305
00:34:07,740 --> 00:34:09,980
Zhang Bin is a cunning old fox.

306
00:34:09,980 --> 00:34:11,860
He must have left himself a way out.

307
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:16,800
He's still stalling here,
so he must be waiting for Liu Bin Bo's men.

308
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:18,160
We must find him soon.

309
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:19,856
We're racing the clock.

310
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:40,073
When people are about to die,
every last one of them gets scared.

311
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:43,363
I thought you were tougher, Chen Yi.

312
00:34:52,620 --> 00:34:54,780
When you kill someone yourself,

313
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:58,806
there's no way your hands don't shake.

314
00:35:10,199 --> 00:35:11,800
Not scared, are we?

315
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,066
Good.

316
00:35:14,220 --> 00:35:16,180
We were brothers once.

317
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:18,146
This day next year,

318
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:23,243
I'll burn three bundles of joss paper for you.

319
00:35:25,420 --> 00:35:26,823
Goodbye, Chen Yi.

320
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:31,360
Chen Yi.

321
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,400
- Chen Yi!
- Miao Jing!

322
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,040
Go.

323
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:36,333
Go.

324
00:35:40,559 --> 00:35:42,200
Miao Jing.

325
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:45,080
Miao Jing.

326
00:36:08,579 --> 00:36:10,179
Chen Yi.

327
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:22,446
Get up here.

328
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:27,626
Stop.

329
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:40,880
Lucky you.

330
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:43,720
This is really goodbye.

331
00:38:18,998 --> 00:38:21,200
Did you miss me?

332
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:23,820
We still have a score to settle.

333
00:38:23,820 --> 00:38:25,020
You!

334
00:38:25,020 --> 00:38:26,243
Zhai.

335
00:38:48,579 --> 00:38:53,683
<i>Before they took me to Country Jin,
Zhai Feng Mao tied me up at the docks.</i>

336
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:59,390
<i>Honestly, I wasn't that scared.</i>

337
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:06,060
<i>I just kept thinking
I never got to say goodbye properly.</i>

338
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:12,970
<i>I never got to hold your hand the way I am now.</i>

339
00:39:20,699 --> 00:39:21,913
<i>Chen Yi.</i>

340
00:39:24,900 --> 00:39:26,526
<i>You're mine.</i>

341
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:39,880
Zhai! Zhai!

342
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:41,060
Stop, please.

343
00:40:41,060 --> 00:40:42,666
Stop, please.

344
00:40:55,739 --> 00:40:56,840
Zhai.

345
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:58,579
Zhai.

346
00:40:58,579 --> 00:40:59,639
- Stop.
- Don't move.

347
00:40:59,639 --> 00:41:02,400
- Don't move.
- Drop the knife.

348
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:03,980
- Drop the knife.
- Drop the knife.

349
00:41:03,980 --> 00:41:06,623
You can't kill me.

350
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:30,046
Jing.

351
00:41:30,739 --> 00:41:32,640
Yi, are you okay?

352
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:34,040
Hurry. Call for backup.

353
00:41:34,040 --> 00:41:36,116
Hurry. Call an ambulance.

354
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:37,460
I...

355
00:42:37,460 --> 00:42:39,280
love...

356
00:42:40,340 --> 00:42:42,040
you.

357
00:42:43,300 --> 00:42:46,440
I love you, too.

358
00:43:04,500 --> 00:43:06,353
[One day ago]

359
00:43:15,580 --> 00:43:19,680
[We'll meet in the light,
where there's no darkness.]

360
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:33,720
[We'll meet in the light,
where there's no darkness.]

